observations.recommendation:
Municipal Engineer issue Certificates of Completion for the completed projects to be used as basis by the Municipal Accountant in the reclassification of these items to their proper PPE accounts;

Municipal Accountant take up the corresponding depreciation expenses of these projects from the time these were completed until December 31, 2023; and

Municipal Accountant reconcile the amounts recorded in the ledger with the amounts incurred to date recorded by the Engineering department so as to present fairly the financial statements of the Municipality as at a given period.

We recommended and Management agreed to ensure that the:
Municipal Engineer, Municipal Accountant and other concerned municipal officials and employees reconcile their respective records, conduct regular monitoring to ensure that fund transfers are implemented and liquidated within the prescribed period;
Municipal Mayor and other concerned officials return or seek authority from the source agencies to realign the excess/unspent balances of the fully implemented projects. Likewise, assess the feasibility/necessity of the projects that remain unimplemented, otherwise return the funds to the source agency;
Municipal accountant carefully analyze the accounts with negative balances and identify the causes thereon and effect the necessary adjustments to reflect the correct balances. Also, effect the following proposed adjusting journal entries:

Municipal Accountant, to:

Trace the movement of the RPT and SET Receivables and corresponding Deferred Credits; 

Segregate from the Report of Monthly Collections the 25% share for the Barangay, 35% for the Province and 40% for the Municipality on RPT-Basic including the 50% sharing between the Province and Municipality on SET;

Prepare JEV for the necessary adjustments on the affected accounts based on the results of segregating the amounts of shares of the Barangays, Province and Municipality;

Prepare the appropriate JEV following the pro-forma entry for tax collections in 2022 and in the succeeding periods in order to come up with the true balance of collectibles from taxpayers as at December 31, 2022; and

Henceforth, submit reconciliation statement, in case there are discrepancies in the recording of receivables, deferred credits and in the recognition of income relative to real property and special education taxes to ensure accurate recording in the books of the LGU.

Municipal Mayor submit:

An acceptable written justification for the hiring of an Individual Contract of Service to perform regular functions of the agency as well as the reasonableness of the compensation that is higher than the salary of comparable positions in government;

A certification relative to the claimed travel allowance that (1) the official missions/ tasks cannot be performed by/or assigned to any other regular/permanent employee; and (2) the tasks/activities are necessary to fulfill the obligations as contained in the contract of service;

A legal basis, if any, on the claim of honoraria amounting to ₱30,000.00 as being one of the members in the committee even in the absence of the entitlement in the contract of service to prevent the issuance of notice of disallowance.

Henceforth, the HRMO exert more effort in filling up the regular position and coordinate with the Civil Service Commission on the advertisement of the vacant positions to increase the prospect of hiring a qualified candidate.

We recommended that Management submit the following documents to support the validity and propriety of the above transactions, viz:
a. Memorandum of Agreement between the Municipality of Alcoy and the Ramon Aboitiz Foundation, Inc (RAFI);
b. All the bidding documents related to the procurement of the labor for the four (4) RAFI projects;
c. Canvass/Quotations of the four (4) Pakyaw Leaders, in the absence of public bidding and justification thereof; 
 d.   Explanation in writing on why part of the RAFI counterpart for the labor amounting to ₱1,150,389.01 was cash advanced by the Municipal Treasurer, when in fact, the labor have already been awarded to the four (4) Pakyaw Contractors;
e.  Inspection and Acceptance Report and Certificate of Turn-over by the RAFI and the LGU of the completed projects;
f. Change or Variation Order to support overpayment of ₱39,750.00, otherwise require refund of the excess amount; 
g. Certificate of Availability of Funds signed by the Municipal Accountant; and
h. Approved budget for Special Education Fund for CY 2015.

We recommended that Management explain in writing why the procurement of goods and services were not bidded out or canvassed but instead were made thru cash advances by the two (2) personnel. Also require the Municipal Treasurer to submit the documents to support propriety of the Socio-cultural expenditures totalling ₱920,783.09 as follows:
a. Program of Work/ Design;
b. Paid payrolls duly approved by concerned Management officials;
c. Purchase Request;
d. Purchase Order;
e. Inspection and Acceptance Report;
f. Statement of Account/Bill for meals, rental of sounds and other services paid;
g. Canvass of at least three (3) suppliers;
h.  List of Participants/Contestants;
i. Official Result signed by designated judges;
j. Schedule of Activities/Games;
k. Accomplishment Report for services rendered by suppliers;
l. Duly approved disbursement vouchers and SB Resolution for the release of funds to eight (8) barangays totalling ₱160,000.00.

