We recommend that Management should:

a.)Stop immediately the practice of granting cash advances on non-existing transactions or based merely on payroll estimates of projects;
b.) Explain fully in writing why this irregular practice of making cash advances for imaginary or payroll estimates were granted;
c.) Also explain on why the Municipal Engineer was the one who signed as to completeness of supporting documents who is not familiar with the required documentation. Instruct the Accountant scrutinize the sufficiency and accuracy of documentation before granting cash advances to any accountable officer.
